  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally obtained money appear legal by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions. Specific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but typically include:\n\n1. Key elements:\n- Concealing the origin of illegally obtained funds\n- Transforming illegal money into seemingly legitimate assets\n- Attempting to disguise the source of criminal proceeds\n\n2. Common legal components:\n- Knowingly engaging in financial transactions with funds from illegal activities\n- Attempting to hide or disguise the nature of criminal proceeds\n- Transferring or converting assets obtained through criminal conduct\n\n3. Typical criminal predicate offenses:\n- Drug trafficking\n- Fraud\n- Corruption\n- Organized crime\n- Terrorism financing\n\n4. International standards typically established by:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF)\n- United Nations conventions\n- Individual national legislation\n\n5. Potential legal penalties:\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant financial fines\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential imprisonment\n\nNote: Specific legal definitions can differ between countries and jurisdictions.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering definitions?",
